<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,289,975]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,394,420]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Measurements.</emphasis>
Total length: 14.8–16.5; head length: 1.8–2.1; head width: 3.0–3.3; pronotal length: 2.6–2.8; pronotal width: 9.2–9.9; scutellum length: 7.3–7.9; scutellum width: 5.0–5.7; abdominal width: 8.4–9.1; length of antennal segments. I: 0.9–1.0; II: 1.7–2.0; III: 1.1–1.5; IV: 4.2–4.8; V: missing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,289,975]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,497,523]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe reaching all of its extension. Anterolateral margin punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with brown to concolorous punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[159,265,567,593]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 20C</figureCitation>
). Body ventrally with brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[691,798,567,593]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 20D</figureCitation>
). Male (
<figureCitation box="[892,1033,567,593]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 14A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore dorsal rim slightly expanded and convex medially (
<figureCitation box="[488,593,602,628]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 14A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup half-moon shaped; adjacent to dorsal rim; partially visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[505,641,636,663]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 14A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere elongated, golf club shaped, inner margin with conspicuous carina ending at rounded apex of posterior lobe (
<figureCitation box="[688,824,671,697]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 14B–C</figureCitation>
). Proctiger with dorsolateral tufts of long setae separat- ed by almost glabrous carina; posterior face pentagonal (
<figureCitation box="[784,922,706,732]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 14A–D</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim median excavation widely open; expansions rounded, setose apically, surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1226,1333,740,767]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 14D</figureCitation>
). Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[264,366,775,801]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[233,1350,195,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-23@24.[220,1367,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 14. Hypoxys similis sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view. E—Female, genital plates (Scale = 1mm)." pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Fig. 14E</figureCitation>
). Valvifers 8 posterior margin arched, inner angle covering more than half of valvifers 9; inner margin divergent in distal third. Valvulae 9 barely exposed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,728,844,871]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,289,975]" box="[199,728,844,871]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,844,870]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Comments.</emphasis>
See comments of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[542,721,844,870]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentagonalis">
<emphasis box="[542,721,844,870]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. pentagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="210" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,289,975]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,879,905]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name refers to the similarity between the dorsal rim of this species and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" box="[1154,1285,880,905]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristatus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1154,1285,880,905]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. cristatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1293,1353,880,906]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes, 2022" authorityName="Nunes &amp; Mendonça &amp; Fernandes" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Hypoxys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentagonalis" status="sp. n">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="210">H. pentagonalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[303,358,914,940]" pageId="23" pageNumber="210" rank="species">sp. n</taxonomicNameLabel>
.. These species show the dorsal margin of the pygophore slightly expanded medially.
</paragraph>
